ce:section.ce:para:
Encouraged by the type I/II ROS production of RCDs in solution, their performance to produce ROS in tumor cells were evaluated. First, DCFH-DA was selected as the green fluorescence probe for O2
                        −• and 1O2 detection. The CLSM results showed that all 4T1 cells treated with the three RCDs emitted green fluorescence with gradually increasing signals from h-RCDs to e-RCDs and p-RCDs (Fig. 4a and 
                           S7
                        ). Subsequently, DHE was used as the specific fluorescent probe to detect O2
                        −• production. The red fluorescence with the similar signal intensity could be observed in each group of 4T1 cells (Fig. 4a and 
                           S8
                        ). Finally, the 1O2 production in 4T1 cells was detected using SOSG as the specific fluorescent probe. Upon 635 nm laser irradiation, the stepwise increasing green fluorescence signals in 4T1 cells could be observed from h-RCDs to e-RCDs to p-RCDs (Fig. 4a and 
                           S9
                        ). All these results were consistent with previous ROS detection in solution, which further confirmed that the as-prepared RCDs could realize tunable increasing 1O2 production while maintaining equal O2
                        −• generation.
